latestIgtvVideos.title: Where to get Parsi food in our #jaipur city ?
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
If you love Parsi, Iranian & Mumbai food, then you gotta watch this video, right now! @akuri.jaipur 

Save & Share this post 😉 

Akuri, our first Parsi cafe with love from #bombay. They opened 16th Aug on the Parsi New Year which is celebrated as NavRooz. Address: K10, Income Tax Colony, Tonk Road. Time : 8am to 11am, every day. ☎️ 830 666 2812. With Wi-fi and air conditioning. 

Parsi restaurant is an integral part of Bombay’s history. Happy to have them here and it was my first experience with this cuisine. We loveeeeed the car in the entrance, their vintage vibes, old Bollywood songs, minimal decor, and history attached to it. We had our breakfast and lunch there and all were #approved . I think they are a super option in Durgapura area. Happy for this neighborhood 🤩

They are recommending us to try : fresh bakery. Drink : Tokhum (my favorite) & Irani Shikanji . Breakfast: House chai and Muska bun (loved) and Akuri (egg and pav). Appetizers: crispy okra fries and Keema Par Eedu (scrambled mutton with eggs). Main course - Salli Paneer with Malabari parantha (we liked),Patra Nu Macchi (fish on banana leaf) or Dhansak Dal (lentils). Berry Pulao (rice with berries). Desserts: Bombay Rosé Falooda. 

It’s the perfect place for a quick meal and is also easy on the pocket. 

Tk you @ronakmaheshwari @foodcraftco & @sambhavg96 for your attention with us! Wishing u all the best 🍀

I want to know which one of you wants to come here?  Share your pictures with the vintage car in the entrance 📸 with us and those who have already come, share your feedback with us, I will love to know 🤩

Adrenaline spikes the moment the race begins.

I don’t understand the data, but I understand my child.

Telemetry? Chassis setup? Understeer? It’s a foreign language for me. But I do understand what it means when he walks off the track frustrated, when he light up after a great session, or when he fights through pain just to finish. And yes, I get emotional.

This sport isn’t just theirs — it becomes ours too. We hope to make lifelong friends with fellow parents, we are learning new skills, and we are discovering our own strength in the process.

Let’s be honest: karting isn’t cheap. The expenses add up quickly — gear, travel, coaching, equipment. But the value goes beyond. It’s in the resilience they will build, the friendships they will make, the discipline they will learn.

Our son Gabriel just completed his first official competition — he started in the very last position, climbed 5 places, drove through pain, and had to dig deep to overcome the effects of strong medication. At one point, he was thrown off the kart — and still, he got up and walked away. He raced clean, and that speaks volumes about his integrity. Gabriel, we’re here — to support you, to believe in you, and to witness every hard-earned position you conquer.

Eu te amo, filho 💕 

Behind every lap Gabriel drove, there was support — from the team @peregrine_racing_india, the coach @ameyawalavalkar who pushed him, to the data analyst @prarthana.murugavel who helped decode his performance, Ponraj, the calm genius in the pits and to the parents who offered advice, encouragement, and honest pep talks — thank you. This journey will be better because of you all.

📸 @_akhilputhiyedath

I’ve always wanted to be a mom.

Becoming a mother was my choice — not something driven by society, family, friends, religion, or anything else. And that makes all the difference.
Because being a mom isn’t easy — we’re constantly questioning if we’re doing the right thing, or what’s truly best for them. And just when we think we’ve figured it out… they grow, change, and move on to the next level — like a video game, aff 😅

Well, Gabriel is an only child, but far from spoiled — wise beyond his years, grounded, and always looking out for others with a heart bigger than words.

He’s honest, trustworthy, and knows right from wrong — and lives by it. He’s a joy to be around — easygoing guy. 

My son, everything we hoped to teach you is already within you. Now it’s your path — and we’ll always be here to support you. I love you unconditionally and I couldn’t be prouder to be your mom.

✨ Happy Mother’s Day to each soul that nurtures, loves, and lifts others up. You are seen. You are appreciated. You matter. 

To all the incredible moms out there — To those raising little ones, to those trying to become moms, to moms-to-be, to pet moms, and even to the women who’ve chosen not to have children. You mother in your own way — and I know you’re nurturing yourself or someone you love deeply. That is motherhood in its truest form.

With love, 
Marcela Baur
